section.t:
 Greylisting implemented at this phase retains a record of
					tuples that combines the provided recipient address with any
					combination of the following: 
						 the source, as described above; 
						 the return email address; 
						 the other recipient addresses of the message (if any)

 Numerous greylisting policies are possible at this point.
					All of them retain a record of tuples that combine the
					various parts of the SMTP transaction in some combination,
					including: 
						 the source, as described above; 
						 the return email address; 
						 the recipients of the message, as a set or
							individually; 
						 identifiers in the message header, such as the contents of
							the RFC5322.From or RFC5322.To fields; 
						 other prominent parts of the content, such as the
							RFC5322.Subject field; 
						 a digest of some or all of the message content, as a
							test for uniqueness; 
						 analysis of arbitrary portions of the message body.
